hdr-mmr.def: The maternal mortality ratio (MMR) is defined as the number of maternal deaths during a given time period per 100,000 live births during the same time period. It depicts the risk of maternal death relative to the number of live births and essentially captures the risk of death in a single pregnancy or a single live birth.
hdr-mmr.name: Maternal Mortality Ratio (deaths per 100,000 live births)
hdr-mmr.source: Calculated based on data in column 1.
